<subSubSection id="5FFD3503CAEDE79D671183FCA9B6D5A5" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="10E1E2F3CE04D70B2D0F9D4DB2297946" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C2C1B120A548B4F1F6A7B6DA51455780" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
The name is a Latin noun, 
<taxonomicName id="B7636BBEF66B7DE42CAAC1399C0CDC88" authorityName="Pham &amp; Karanovic" authorityYear="2022" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope singula" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="singula">
<emphasis id="B3D1E27EB46DCA5D41DD6DE889408C75" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope singula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because only a female has been collected. The name is in nominative, feminine singular, agreeing in gender with the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C84F928E484CA56F66BDD9FCE135A7AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="04F31D1D3740E23CC57D51DF3FFDF4DE" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D65A5255D020C649822A1C82D8C41AC" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Surface of the shell completely smooth. Anterior end with a deep incisure and posterior infold of the carapace with a broad shelf. Posterior end wider than anterior. Dorsal margin rounded. Lateral eye well developed with black pigmented ommatidia. Uropodal lamellae with nine claws.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="360E7CD3C291A2E80F3181C95BD52021" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="FA5B85AE08D825E2C2DA9E96E75F907C" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B3BA0138AB4DB28DB0D08B794CD84197" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="B21DF3955AB426CDE745EC637294F00C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Female.</emphasis>
Shell (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CDC681B9C2A420816EDD01546FAB10E3" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Light microscopy and scanning electron microscopy images of Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a Lateral view from left valve b Internal view from left valve c External view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672096" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">8</figureCitation>
). Carapace oval, broadening at posterior, greatest height near middle, carapace length 1.25 mm, height 0.9 mm. Carapace smooth and without ornamentation.
</paragraph>
<caption id="914197613BCB17F4B0568A71961BC021" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672096" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" start="Figure 8" startId="F8">
<paragraph id="004E8E020C9FC7EC9FC7E9937EAF03C6" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="E8BE88540CA24213F5B7028F75084F94" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Figure 8.</emphasis>
Light microscopy and scanning electron microscopy images of 
<taxonomicName id="4508BBF73A68D9B082A6DBF42408639E" authorityName="Pham &amp; Karanovic" authorityYear="2022" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope singula" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="singula">
<emphasis id="28E2B4665C23DF2C01B6F7E38EB76FA5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope singula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. holotype female adult: 
<emphasis id="8DABA01FBD52A38286984E1729AB57E9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">a</emphasis>
Lateral view from left valve 
<emphasis id="C931935B414A46EB9F8EB69A156F538E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">b</emphasis>
Internal view from left valve 
<emphasis id="1B3C286DEC92D715D3BDCF68B887F11A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">c</emphasis>
External view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="35B06731535AC431E10C85DDBD48806E" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
A1 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BE108A26A1F5D87C654171436566C465" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Light microscopy and scanning electron microscopy images of Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a Lateral view from left valve b Internal view from left valve c External view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672096" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">8a</figureCitation>
). 1st joint: with no hair on broad surface. 2nd joint: one spinous dorsal seta, one short lateral bristle, and small proximal dorsal spines. 3rd joint: seven setae (one short ventral and six dorsal). 4th joint: three bristles (one long dorsal bristle and two short ventral bristles). 5th joint: sensory bristle with six filaments without short proximal terminal. 6th joint: one medial seta, attached to bottom of 7th joint boundary. 7th joint: a-bristle claw-like, bare; b-seta with marginal filaments; c-seta with marginal filaments. 8th joint: d-bristle absent; e-bristle bare with blunt tip; f- and g-bristles with marginal filaments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD7DD57601B9819DA5EAEBFCFA3C41E3" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Bellonci orange (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6EC9A3497EDB555A0DE5366CB8AC26BA" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b bellonci organ c A 2 endopodite d A 2 exopodite e Md basale and coxale endite f Md basale endite g Md endopodite h L 5 i L 6 k L 7 l F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">9b</figureCitation>
). Elongate with rounded tip with unclear constriction.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E839F1A7CD94A675441F1B9FEA10C1ED" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="0CA12F930528F1DED177D4E7D7EB6E14" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="C5EC6025E79D07B365DD96E68C4E5DF7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Eyes</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Lateral eye with 18 ommatidia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="894FEBD9953916A6EF0F47CADD1AF2A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
A2 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6B9DA14E9B0C2BC0DDA25BA514A32182" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b bellonci organ c A 2 endopodite d A 2 exopodite e Md basale and coxale endite f Md basale endite g Md endopodite h L 5 i L 6 k L 7 l F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">9c, d</figureCitation>
). Protopodite: rounded without medial bristle. Endopodite (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1A95782D242B4BA12728B925A64EF83A" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b bellonci organ c A 2 endopodite d A 2 exopodite e Md basale and coxale endite f Md basale endite g Md endopodite h L 5 i L 6 k L 7 l F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">9c</figureCitation>
): not strongly jointed, with long terminal bristle. Exopodite (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="160FA1F5B55F05B1CEA2D62FC2387B7B" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b bellonci organ c A 2 endopodite d A 2 exopodite e Md basale and coxale endite f Md basale endite g Md endopodite h L 5 i L 6 k L 7 l F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">9d</figureCitation>
): 9-jointed; bristle of 2nd segment along ventral margin and spines along dorsal margin reaching 8th joint; 3rd-8th joints with natatory hairs and spines along proximal part of ventral margin. 9th article: four bristles (two long natatory and two short bristles). 4th-8th joints with minute spines at inner terminal corner.
</paragraph>
<caption id="139D8E24A3E42CF10A9467C185154353" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" start="Figure 9" startId="F9">
<paragraph id="226955DF435E44E1FE9CF0F946FAF4D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="BECC9E48523A065DFF8CB64483ABE974" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Figure 9.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="323C4F75F341C3AC3925CF290154C20B" authorityName="Pham &amp; Karanovic" authorityYear="2022" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope singula" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="singula">
<emphasis id="1644233C3FFF965FC5EF8D74FA7C62BF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope singula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. holotype female adult: 
<emphasis id="E200A4319C251F6C58590AD3A7B50DFD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">a</emphasis>
A1 
<emphasis id="85F86868626DB8422B231245417FC042" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">b</emphasis>
bellonci organ 
<emphasis id="89453EFD1CCCB682E954D2D59207264F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">c</emphasis>
A2 endopodite 
<emphasis id="BAD92B1E44300DB35D94BCAE1E7FFD7B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">d</emphasis>
A2 exopodite 
<emphasis id="6F0A500D3C324B1FC2B311A3FDCB53A6" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">e</emphasis>
Md basale and coxale endite 
<emphasis id="BD5A0E8EB0504E68048F64E5C8971048" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">f</emphasis>
Md basale endite 
<emphasis id="988FD17263620F18EB601A6C8FE6102A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">g</emphasis>
Md endopodite 
<emphasis id="29CB6FDDFCCB084F24515C6A4CC79587" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">h</emphasis>
L5 
<emphasis id="6DC1851A7F511EFCD471CA3120277DA7" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">i</emphasis>
L6 
<emphasis id="31307F23FD943A532581594EE5E90446" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">k</emphasis>
L7 
<emphasis id="30386E2FD0885157061C7ECA12C5DC3A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">l</emphasis>
F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="4A3BD0DA0C7F63BD2936BBDE908F0C37" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Md (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="725DB1D7318DAF742B0B167950E34DB7" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b bellonci organ c A 2 endopodite d A 2 exopodite e Md basale and coxale endite f Md basale endite g Md endopodite h L 5 i L 6 k L 7 l F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">9e-g</figureCitation>
). Coxale endite (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="42D96D251C6A7794A3D8DB699A6AA346" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b bellonci organ c A 2 endopodite d A 2 exopodite e Md basale and coxale endite f Md basale endite g Md endopodite h L 5 i L 6 k L 7 l F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">9e</figureCitation>
) same as that on 
<taxonomicName id="237179E430B198E4BFF147131638F76D" genus="P." lsidName="P. busanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="busanensis">
<emphasis id="DFAF5C420D0FDC91DB154518A91A7AC4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. busanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Basale (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="18FB9DF64A9E8AE221CE60A300B93EA6" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b bellonci organ c A 2 endopodite d A 2 exopodite e Md basale and coxale endite f Md basale endite g Md endopodite h L 5 i L 6 k L 7 l F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">9f</figureCitation>
): Basale endite with three spinous end bristles, four triaenid bristles with three spines excluding terminal pair, and two equal-length bare bristles. Basale dorsal margin with two long terminal setae, without mid-bristle; five rows of small spines on the broad surface near dorsal margin. Exopodite with hirsute tip and two small subterminal setae, exopodite almost same length as dorsal margin of first endopodite article. Endopodite (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B96A716F58ADD0C52544300F06D77798" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b bellonci organ c A 2 endopodite d A 2 exopodite e Md basale and coxale endite f Md basale endite g Md endopodite h L 5 i L 6 k L 7 l F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">9g</figureCitation>
): 1st joint: ventral margin with three bristles (two long with long marginal spines, and one shorter without spine or hair); 2nd joint: ventral margin: with three terminal bristles; dorsal margin: with stout a-, b-, c-, and d-bristles and without bristle proximal to a-bristle; one long e-bristle between b- and c-bristles; four medial bristles forming an oblique row adjacent to c-bristle; f-bristle between c- and d-bristles, long, bare; g-bristle longer than f-bristle. 3rd segment with a strong dorsal claw-like bristle without marginal spines, three juxtaposed stout bristles of equal length, and two thin bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="47ECBEEBCB412374760851E1A18E5284" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
Mxl. Endite I with three bristles. Endite II with three bristles. Basale: one dorsal medial distal bristle, two ventral medial proximal bristles. Endopodite: 1st with one short 
<normalizedToken id="6495718DAB4DCFC4FBFF9CC4A5B84B30" originalValue="α-seta">α-seta</normalizedToken>
and one hairy 
<normalizedToken id="B23E6F18DE9BCE9CC0DC326FB655B746" originalValue="β-seta">β-seta</normalizedToken>
; 2nd article with two terminal bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ABFBB33728325DA68DC8C77100BAF71B" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
L5 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C0837264CE48DD5731A334174882621F" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b bellonci organ c A 2 endopodite d A 2 exopodite e Md basale and coxale endite f Md basale endite g Md endopodite h L 5 i L 6 k L 7 l F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">9h</figureCitation>
). Ventral section with fan of long setae. Comb with spinous exopodal bristle just reaching past distal end of comb, one short slender bristle just ventral to base of stout bristle, one bristle near exopodal bristle stem, and four lateral bristles set back from edge at comb mid length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="12D8F36F3073ABE7A3295D4CAE23CBC6" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
L6 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="25DDB91D19C361629FDD25E895EC7E32" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b bellonci organ c A 2 endopodite d A 2 exopodite e Md basale and coxale endite f Md basale endite g Md endopodite h L 5 i L 6 k L 7 l F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">9i</figureCitation>
). Unidentified number of endite bristle on the anterior margin. Lateral flap with hairs but no bristles. Anterior tip of skirt with two small bristles. Ventral and postero-ventral margin with 17 plumose bristles (one missing).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A9B7D29521D6E9E029F113239B4984E" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
L7 (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C5CFAC132C1B851924AB77B95319B89B" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b bellonci organ c A 2 endopodite d A 2 exopodite e Md basale and coxale endite f Md basale endite g Md endopodite h L 5 i L 6 k L 7 l F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">9k</figureCitation>
). Each limb with ten bristles. Four proximal and six distal bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="682641347C9006BF6DF81D358168B2AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
F (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="75332BE93C98C308DF31C3EAA6EF4164" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Parasterope singula sp. nov. holotype female adult: a A 1 b bellonci organ c A 2 endopodite d A 2 exopodite e Md basale and coxale endite f Md basale endite g Md endopodite h L 5 i L 6 k L 7 l F. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.77996.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672097" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">9l</figureCitation>
). Each lamella with six claws plus three posterior claws bristle-like. A total of nine claws and bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="535CE7FC9F2ECA10C19DAF4346161F51" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="45475C90B3B4C9981398C4A2FA930D79" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Male.</emphasis>
Not collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FB7A6643C6E93B1BBA821EA0877A18A9" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="A340AA4A942BA558FD4A74309718DC13" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C61271B00118570D4CEFAA6C35C497B1" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
The presence of rows of small spines on the broad surface near the dorsal margin of the Md basale is a unique feature of 
<taxonomicName id="19B4722EDC905E8B8D392E44A1A792DD" authorityName="Pham &amp; Karanovic" authorityYear="2022" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope singula" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="singula">
<emphasis id="B2F755068DD24BB5EA9944FA452AAFDA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope singula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, the number of bristles on the L7 (ten bristles: four on the terminal segment (two on each side), six on the proximal segments (three on each side) is less than in all other 
<taxonomicName id="C476A7709C98FDCDC24E393935A62729" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8E52FBDD0AE6A5E95740092CCAEEAB65" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
representatives. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="1EF1F750A2A369724F608228DC792E18" genus="P." lsidName="P. mckenziei" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="mckenziei">
<emphasis id="743D7B610BDDD5107CB698A03198B0ED" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. mckenziei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described from Samar Province, Philippines (McKenzie, 1970) but differs in the following characters: the Md endopodite is without a proximal bristle next to the a-bristle, a character not known in any other 
<taxonomicName id="BA5A2D072497F87DB0EEA099EA9F9B0D" class="Ostracoda" family="Cylindroleberididae" genus="Parasterope" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parasterope" order="Myodocopida" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7F751A1060B44219C7DD1EA6D0E637A8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Parasterope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the number of claws on UL (nine vs. seven).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FB43B93D65D6557EB3A2A53702BDF515" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
The 2nd joint of the Md endopodite in 
<taxonomicName id="12BB96B499B3BD507AE8191DAF22CA46" genus="P." lsidName="P. singula" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="singula">
<emphasis id="DC28E6B923FBE38640FEE0AE71B2DF96" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. singula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
carries one oblique row of cleaning setae, also recorded in 
<taxonomicName id="0EB46BA956E83E701F334D859661F574" genus="P." lsidName="P. antyx" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="antyx">
<emphasis id="1250F72A14E86EC4496B93C77EEEAF45" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. antyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kornicker, 1989 from Bay of Biscay (Kornicker, 1989), 
<taxonomicName id="AA111F76C0B08FD16D7E5B07EA0DD1C7" genus="P." lsidName="P. gamma" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="gamma">
<emphasis id="2F11A6CE99BECEA8E82C76641D186314" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. gamma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kornicker, Harrison-Nelson &amp; Coles, 2007 from Hawaiian Islands (
<bibRefCitation id="0034B90A3C24BE5DFBA6FE54D9AC8CBB" author="Kornicker, LS" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum bulletin in Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B23" refString="Kornicker, LS, Harrison-Nelson, E, Coles, SL, 2007. Ostracoda (Myodocopina) from O'ahu and French Frigate Shoals, Hawaiian Islands. Bishop Museum bulletin in Zoology 8: 1 - 128" title="Ostracoda (Myodocopina) from O'ahu and French Frigate Shoals, Hawaiian Islands." volume="8" year="2007">Kornicker et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="F4CD293682DC654C4DBDD9C171386E62" genus="P." lsidName="P. hulingsi" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="hulingsi">
<emphasis id="5F93B5803FA4A0FD9724CD803CD956B3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. hulingsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Baker, 1978 from California (
<bibRefCitation id="9BACE99CE610E83CCC0F77A8972DB1BA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1163/156854078X00042" author="Baker, JH" journalOrPublisher="Crustaceana" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="139 - 151" refId="B1" refString="Baker, JH, 1978. Two new species of Parasterope (Myodocopina, Ostracoda) from southern California. Crustaceana 35 (2): 139 - 151, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1163/156854078X00042" title="Two new species of Parasterope (Myodocopina, Ostracoda) from southern California." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/156854078X00042" volume="35" year="1978">Baker 1978</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="5143A16C8AECF09DF3828B776514FDFE" genus="P." lsidName="P. jenseni" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="jenseni">
<emphasis id="66E20E7E0F6F399C9DF5DF3B63D76C70" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. jenseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Sagami Sea, Japan (
<bibRefCitation id="683521DD233DADA0D322F11C509095DB" author="Poulsen, EM" journalOrPublisher="Marine Biodiversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" refId="B33" refString="Poulsen, EM, 1965. Ostracoda - Myodocopa, Part II: Cypridiniformes - Rutidermatidae, Sarsiellidae and Asteropidae. Dana Report Carlsberg Foundation (65): 1-484." title="Ostracoda - Myodocopa, Part II: Cypridiniformes - Rutidermatidae, Sarsiellidae and Asteropidae. Dana Report Carlsberg Foundation (65): 1 - 484." year="1965">Poulsen 1965</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="5F72960A56ACD21A8F08202173F900AA" genus="P." lsidName="P. lagunicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="lagunicola">
<emphasis id="5579D5AD14008563B6A2FF6D7FC6C36B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. lagunicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hartmann, 1984 from French Polynesia (
<bibRefCitation id="74AB3A6FBFDDCB6FD41E1043AC53ECAB" author="Hartmann, G" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="117 - 169" refId="B10" refString="Hartmann, G, 1984. Zur Kenntnis der Ostracoden der polynesischen Inseln Huahine (Gesellschaftsinseln) und Rangiroa (Tuamotu-Inseln). Mit Bemerkungen zur Verbreitung und Ausbreitung litoraler Ostracoden und einer Uebersicht ueber die bislang auf den pazifischen Inseln gefunden. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut 81: 117 - 169" title="Zur Kenntnis der Ostracoden der polynesischen Inseln Huahine (Gesellschaftsinseln) und Rangiroa (Tuamotu-Inseln). Mit Bemerkungen zur Verbreitung und Ausbreitung litoraler Ostracoden und einer Uebersicht ueber die bislang auf den pazifischen Inseln gefunden." volume="81" year="1984">Hartmann 1984</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4382FFE45F50BD06126AEF30D39FA510" genus="P." lsidName="P. mckenziei" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="mckenziei">
<emphasis id="340F3E274AAD1D3B39AA0BE5997F85EC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. mckenziei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Philippines (
<bibRefCitation id="E4BA619BC472B0E42E834FA6CA57B7D9" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.39" author="Kornicker, LS" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 32" refId="B15" refString="Kornicker, LS, 1970. Myodocopid Ostracoda (Cypridinacea) from the Philippine Islands. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 39: 1 - 32, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.39" title="Myodocopid Ostracoda (Cypridinacea) from the Philippine Islands." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.39" volume="39" year="1970">Kornicker 1970</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="B0796E443F63975A75585F9536F3F567" genus="P." lsidName="P. muelleri" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="muelleri">
<emphasis id="6114906DF73BC1372188E486269B8579" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. muelleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Skogsberg, 1920 from England (
<bibRefCitation id="738F03D10C5C04EC5EB4040F7316ED15" author="Poulsen, EM" journalOrPublisher="Marine Biodiversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" refId="B33" refString="Poulsen, EM, 1965. Ostracoda - Myodocopa, Part II: Cypridiniformes - Rutidermatidae, Sarsiellidae and Asteropidae. Dana Report Carlsberg Foundation (65): 1-484." title="Ostracoda - Myodocopa, Part II: Cypridiniformes - Rutidermatidae, Sarsiellidae and Asteropidae. Dana Report Carlsberg Foundation (65): 1 - 484." year="1965">Poulsen 1965</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="A27F87DEEDEE1A68ED0E03C1493A4F16" genus="P." lsidName="P. prolixa" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="prolixa">
<emphasis id="7BBC58475FBA75DC113EF912FED4514F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. prolixa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kornicker, 1975 from Australia (
<bibRefCitation id="CDE4F608573E18159FF20C3526231F29" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.163" author="Kornicker, LS" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="375 - 720" refId="B16" refString="Kornicker, LS, 1975. Antarctic Ostracoda (Myodocopina), Part 2. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 163: 375 - 720, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.163" title="Antarctic Ostracoda (Myodocopina), Part 2." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.163" volume="163" year="1975">Kornicker 1975</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="A6E14E3A2B81E4CA7E3FD5C3ABBB7994" genus="P." lsidName="P. sequex" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="sequex">
<emphasis id="B9719F4509A551B5EE5C0C86FB2A5573" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. sequex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kornicker &amp; Poore, 1996 from Australia (
<bibRefCitation id="152997D9EBAF0A2A051B2B9FDAF601A3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.573" author="Kornicker, LS" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 186" refId="B22" refString="Kornicker, LS, Poore, GC, 1996. Ostracoda (Myodocopina) of the SE Australian Continental Slope: Part 3. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 573: 1 - 186, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.573" title="Ostracoda (Myodocopina) of the SE Australian Continental Slope: Part 3." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.573" volume="573" year="1996">Kornicker and Poore 1996</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="2E1EF1EAA60BD13190F0B4FA1F81883D" genus="P." lsidName="P. styx" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="styx">
<emphasis id="98B811CE31E8C498D9529B48A922BFEC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. styx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Chile (
<bibRefCitation id="13FC3C62A1E3C5ECB7F9FF02CB636D7E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.163" author="Kornicker, LS" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="375 - 720" refId="B16" refString="Kornicker, LS, 1975. Antarctic Ostracoda (Myodocopina), Part 2. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 163: 375 - 720, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.163" title="Antarctic Ostracoda (Myodocopina), Part 2." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.163" volume="163" year="1975">Kornicker 1975</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="AA9D6F21A8AB11039880041B98FED22D" genus="P." lsidName="P. theta" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="theta">
<emphasis id="A2F26E2AC1BAA529B0EBA699489F60DC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. theta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<normalizedToken id="C971517D330A0A881820E9E53A01DFE5" originalValue="Waikïkï">Waikiki</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8A3F4A3CD5291878910C6D858B24A4A3" author="Kornicker, LS" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum bulletin in Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B23" refString="Kornicker, LS, Harrison-Nelson, E, Coles, SL, 2007. Ostracoda (Myodocopina) from O'ahu and French Frigate Shoals, Hawaiian Islands. Bishop Museum bulletin in Zoology 8: 1 - 128" title="Ostracoda (Myodocopina) from O'ahu and French Frigate Shoals, Hawaiian Islands." volume="8" year="2007">Kornicker et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). The three other new species, 
<taxonomicName id="2CE71B6B64E2FCDA74500B687797B257" genus="P." lsidName="P. busanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="busanensis">
<emphasis id="5491A610727F9CA4D84B04EE7F287980" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. busanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5197AC872B0B9BE5A8C6BC32C79D7553" genus="P." lsidName="P. sagami" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="sagami">
<emphasis id="7D642C254B751549E40A779A0468F129" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. sagami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="A7D05D219A60AAFB2F9C4968AD4A64B3" genus="P." lsidName="P. sohi" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="sohi">
<emphasis id="40542AEA3A68E2AD467980B9F6089F00" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. sohi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also have two oblique rows. The exopodite of the A2 in 
<taxonomicName id="2D1D07477ADD8826E551630B1D4C8797" genus="P." lsidName="P. singula" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="singula">
<emphasis id="5783A1DAF29B1200C6B930C97EA7246A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. singula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0C1C1213395144F31922E524EA7BB2FD" genus="P." lsidName="P. sohi" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="sohi">
<emphasis id="22FF2E3BC789D24E9D78AFAA4525F761" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. sohi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
carries minute spines at inner terminal corner on the 5th-8th joints, while these spines are present from the 1st-8th joints in 
<taxonomicName id="8ABB2FBF3475A319DD661D7B920B670F" genus="P." lsidName="P. busanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="busanensis">
<emphasis id="58BDC7F7F1B76DF0E310AD14EC9F487D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. busanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="418130C4FAF9AE2630F6765108BD196C" genus="P." lsidName="P. sagami" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" rank="species" species="sagami">
<emphasis id="DDA2F376A48A40EEB6A996137557B604" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">P. sagami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="477FE87A75142C6F9E5D0F83FEAB4BEE" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">GenBank numbers 16S: OK048686, OK048687; 18S OK048723.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
